result.execSummary:
The defendant Tracie N Wasley was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • OWI (3rd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Tracie N Wasley in court with Attorney Cameron Weitzner.  Timothy Suha appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court quashes warrant. Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count #2.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #2.  Count #1 is dismissed and read-in.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Weitzner makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #2: HUBER:  90 days (7 days credit), LAST 45 DAYS STAYED.   Huber with standard release conditions.  Defendant taken into custody.

DAY REPORT CENTER:  75 DAYS, Consecutive to Huber sentence.  Good time not allowed on DRC.  If defendant successfully completes Day Report Center, the 45 days of Huber stayed will be permanently stayed. 

FINE: $1,544.00 & $200.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid out of cash bail posted ($1,300.00) and remainder due at rate of $25.00 per month commencing 10/3/16 or serve 10 days jail, consecutive, as penalty for non payment of fine)

**Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.**

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35.00 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forwarded to Waukesha County Sheriff's Department. 

DL REVOCATION:  27 months

IGNITION INTERLOCK:  27 months  -  NOTE:  Court grants request for 1/2 Price IID. 

Victim Impact Panel on:  11/9/16. Defendant to serve 30 days huber, consecutive, as penalty for failure to attend Victim Impact Panel.

Other:  AODA ASSESSMENT AND FOLLOW THROUGH
